<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,746,2012]" box="[151,1436,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">The Nearctic fauna is poorly documented and badly in need of both collection and revision. A major problem</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,746,2012]" box="[151,1436,786,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
is that many Nearctic species are known only from females. The current keys (
<bibRefCitation author="Parent" box="[1087,1233,786,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" refString="Parent, O. (1929) Etudes sur les Dolichopodides. Encyclopedie Entomologique. Serie B. II. Diptera, 5, 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1929">
Parent 
<number box="[1172,1233,786,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1929.0">1929</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson" box="[1247,1428,786,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" refString="Robinson, H. (1964) A synopsis of the Dolichopodidae (Diptera) of the southeastern United States and adjacent regions. Entomological Society of America Miscellaneous Publications, 4, 103 - 192." type="journal article" year="1964">
Robinson 
<number box="[1368,1428,786,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,746,2012]" box="[151,1436,826,852]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">are unreliable, since they are based on a mix of male and female characters (leg color, for example, can be sex-</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,746,2012]" box="[151,524,866,892]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
ually dimorphic in 
<taxonomicName box="[374,507,866,891]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[374,507,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Mesorhaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
